defaultThe effectiveness of Cdefaultommissioners in reducing crime and delivering an effective police service within their police force areadefault&#xa0;
default2.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Police and Crime P
defaultlan I 
defaulthave 
defaultdeveloped aims to empower police and other agencies to work together to build safer communities in Greater Manchester. In an era of austerity, with 
defaultsignificant
default cuts to the police service and other bodies, working in partnership
default with other agencies
default is key to delivering effective policing
default and safer communities
default. I have been able to bring partnership agencies toge
defaultther in a way that simply did not
default happen before I was elected. Complex issues such as child sexual exploitation or domestic violence are challenges the police 
defaultcannot
default deal with on their own. And this is where Commissioners can be pivotal. Having one local, democratically-accountable figure who takes a strategic view across both the criminal justice system and the community safety agenda, who brings different agencies together around the table to find better ways of working, is central
default to improving confidence in police and other agencies, and making our communities safer
default. And here in Greater Manchester, this 
defaultis not just a talking shop – we are
default delivering real change for the people I represent.
default&#xa0;
default2.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe neighbourhood policing model also sits at the heart of delivering effective policing, and this is something that the Chief Constable and I are determined to ensure remains embedded into the culture and practice of GMP. I used
default a
default modest increase in the police precept (10p per week for the average bill) to support the frontline. The £3.3m generated from the precept increase has been used to bolster neighbourhood policing, creating new neighbourhood police 
defaultofficers and support staff.
default&#xa0;
default2.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultI have
default also introduced new ways of holding the police to account. For a long time the target culture 
defaultwas the main way in which police performance could be measured. I believe this is a flawed model, and have
default done away with 
defaulttargets
default, preferring instead new, meatier performance reports taking a more rounded view. We examine 
defaultwhat crimes are going up, what is
default going down and what the trends are. This helps identify areas where more work is needed and is much more effective than a targets regime. It’s intelligent monitoring of intelligent policing.
default&#xa0;
default2.4.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAlongside this new way to monitor performance, I have introduced parliamentary-style forums which take a detailed look at issues of significant public interest
default (see below)
default. I hav
defaulte also ensured that the public gets regular opportunities to question directly the Chief Constable and me, for example at public meetings, which I have held throughout Greater Manchester since being elected.
default&#xa0;
default3.0.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
